  <section class="projects">
    <h3>RFID-Based Smart Car Gate Opener</h3>
    
    <div class="project-description">
      <p>This project involved designing and implementing an automated security gate system using **RFID (Radio Frequency Identification)** technology. The system is designed to provide hands-free, secure access for vehicles by identifying authorized RFID tags and controlling a motorized gate mechanism.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section-title">
      <h4>Engineering Challenges & Solutions</h4>
    </div>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Signal Integrity & Range:</strong> Optimized the placement of the RFID reader antenna to ensure reliable tag detection through vehicle windshields without interference from the metal chassis.</li>
      <li><strong>Motor Control Logic:</strong> Developed precise timing and safety logic to control the gate's actuator, including "Auto-Close" functionality and emergency stop triggers.</li>
      <li><strong>Power Management:</strong> Integrated a voltage regulation system to ensure the microcontroller and sensors received stable power from a common 12V automotive-style source.</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="section-title">
      <h4>Technical Specifications</h4>
    </div>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Controller:</strong> Arduino/ATmega328P based control logic.</li>
      <li><strong>Sensors:</strong> MFRC522 RFID module for 13.56 MHz frequency detection.</li>
      <li><strong>Actuation:</strong> Servo or DC motor integration with H-Bridge driver for bidirectional gate movement.</li>
      <li><strong>Security:</strong> Encrypted unique ID (UID) verification to prevent unauthorized duplication of gate access.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

